This is Lucianus, the king’s nephew in the play.
You’re an expert commentator, aren’t you?
Yes.
I could even supply the dialogue between you and your lover if you did your little puppet show of love for me.
Ooh, you’re sharp.
Yes, pointy, but you could take the edge off me— though it might make you moan a little.
You get better in your jokes and worse in your manners.
That’s what you women get when you trick us into marriage.—Let’s get started, murderer on stage, please!
Damn it, stop fussing with the makeup, and get going.
We’re all waiting for the revenge!  
